# memory

Durable session + project memory for the chat front-end. Separate from the
prompt registry and from the deterministic benchmark path.

## Must
- Session transcripts live under `~/.luxe/sessions/<session_id>/` (`meta.json` +
  append-only `transcript.jsonl` + `fold.jsonl`), mirroring `run_state.py` idioms
- `gc_sessions` default eviction: keep the most recent 50 sessions AND drop
  anything older than 30 days
- Project memory has two tiers with explicit confidence:
  - repo-local `<repo>/.luxe/memory.md` — user-curated, committable, priority,
    ALWAYS injected
  - `~/.luxe/memory/<project_hash>/facts.jsonl` — auto-captured, `confidence: auto`,
    NEVER injected until promoted to `confidence: manual`
  - `project_hash = sha256(abspath(repo_root))[:12]`
- Memory is injected ONLY as the `<project_memory>` block inside `run_single`'s
  `extra_context`, NEVER by editing `PROMPT_REGISTRY` or the `system_prompt`
- `run_single`'s `extra_context` defaults to "" → byte-identical to legacy when
  no memory/conversation is present

## Must not
- Read or write `~/.claude/` (Claude Code's own memory)
- Read the repo-root `CLAUDE.md` (Claude Code's project-memory file; names are
  close enough to invite a refactor mistake)
- Touch `src/luxe/agents/prompts.py` or `src/luxe/agents/loop.py` (memory injects
  only via `run_single`'s `extra_context`, never the registry or the loop)

## Owns
- src/luxe/memory/**
